feat: imperial prose localization, map upgrades, idle prefetch

Three-pass improvement for the Surface Pro 5 use case.

Pass A — prose unit localization for imperial readers.
  useProse() now rewrites m->ft, mm->in, cm->in, km->mi and km/h->mph in
  every piece of editorial text, not just C->F. Includes a range
  handler (300-600 m -> 984-1,968 ft), a km/h-before-km pass (winds
  25 km/h -> 16 mph), and elevation-context detection so that bare
  metres only convert when the surrounding words signal a vertical
  measurement ("sits at", "perches at", "over", "elevation", ...).
  Verified against the full 187-string corpus (0 leftover C tokens,
  0 leftover metric distance tokens) and 28 targeted unit tests
  including false-positive guards ("10 minutes", "Koppen BSk",
  "mm-level").

Pass B - map visual upgrades, all zero-rerender.
  - Country labels (UNITED STATES / CANADA / MEXICO) projected once
    and placed inside the pan/zoom group so they ride with the map.
    Opacity fades out at higher zoom so they don't compete with
    marker labels.
  - Graticule tick labels (30N/45N/60N, 120W/100W/80W) at the
    continent's edge.
  - Live scale bar that tracks both zoom and the imperial/metric
    toggle. Step chosen from a nice-number ladder; updated
    imperatively via DOM ref instead of triggering a React render.
  - Full 4-point compass rose (N/E/S/W) with dashed inner ring.
  - Cursor lat/lon readout mutated via RAF-coalesced direct-DOM
    updates - no React reconciliation on pointer move.

Pass C - performance.
  - content-visibility: auto on .place-card with contain-intrinsic-size
    so offscreen cards pay no paint/render cost.
  - Idle-time prefetch (requestIdleCallback) of every lazy chunk
    (PlaceDetail, CompareView, CollectionsView, LearnMode) after the
    main thread settles, so first interaction is instant.

Pass D - sparkle.
  - Keyboard-shortcut hints (+ - 0 arrow keys) appended to the map
    legend.

Typechecks, lints, full corpus tests, and production build all clean.
